document_data.History:
The ''deafness'' spell was developed by [[Netheril|Netherese]] arcanist [[Cragh]] of [[Northreach]], himself deaf since birth, in [[-1999 DR|1860 NY (−1999 DR)]] as '''''Cragh's deafness'''''. It was his only spell.<ref> ''blindness'' was an invention of his prolific colleague [[Smolyn]] in [[-1964 DR|1895 NY (−1964 DR)]], then accordingly named '''''Smolyn's blindness'''''.

By the [[1360 DR|1360s DR]] both spells were uncommon among magic-users in [[Faerûn]]<ref> and widespread among those in [[Zakhara]].<ref><ref>{{AQ-time}}

In [[1372 DR|1372 DR, the Year of Wild Magic]], a combined version came into use in the magical community, quickly replacing the two more restrictive spells.
